    "created_at": "2023-01-04T13:47:04Z",
    "updated_at": "2023-01-04T13:47:04Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "@kushalbabel I looked into this a bit and I realized that this started happening to you because the default hardfork in the latest version is the `merge` hardfork, which doesn't assign block rewards to the coinbase address. So a temporary workaround is to change it to London:\r\n\r\n```\r\nnetworks: {\r\n  hardhat: {\r\n    hardfork: \"london\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nI'm not sure if we should consider this expected behavior or not. My first guess is that it's not, because anyone relying on the block rewards behavior (like you) would expect for it to continue working.\r\n\r\nI will open a new issue to research this a bit more and make a decision about it.",
